abstract: Switzerland's bank watchdog is stepping up an inquiry into staff surveillance at Credit Suisse, it said on Friday, as pressure mounts on the bank to explain a second alleged instance of an executive being tailed.
snippet: Switzerland's bank watchdog is stepping up an inquiry into staff surveillance at Credit Suisse, it said on Friday, as pressure mounts on the bank to explain a second alleged instance of an executive being tailed.
lead_paragraph: ZURICH — Switzerland's bank watchdog is stepping up an inquiry into staff surveillance at Credit Suisse, it said on Friday, as pressure mounts on the bank to explain a second alleged instance of an executive being tailed.
headline_main: Credit Suisse Under Fire as Swiss Watchdog Steps Up Snooping Scrutiny
headline_print_headline: Credit Suisse Under Fire as Swiss Watchdog Steps Up Snooping Scrutiny

abstract: Amazon.com Inc plans to raise the fees it charges merchants for warehousing and shipping their goods in the United States by an average 3% next year, the company said Friday, as it faces higher costs from infrastructure and programs such as one-day delivery.
snippet: Amazon.com Inc plans to raise the fees it charges merchants for warehousing and shipping their goods in the United States by an average 3% next year, the company said Friday, as it faces higher costs from infrastructure and programs such as one-da...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Amazon.com Inc plans to raise the fees it charges merchants for warehousing and shipping their goods in the United States by an average 3% next year, the company said Friday, as it faces higher costs from infrastructure and programs such as one-day delivery.
headline_main: Amazon to Raise U.S. Fulfillment Fees 3 Percent for Merchants Next Year
headline_print_headline: Amazon to Raise U.S. Fulfillment Fees 3 Percent for Merchants Next Year

abstract: Russia's Gazprom and Ukraine's Naftogaz will sign a new five-year agreement on transit of Russian gas to Europe via Ukraine, the RIA news agency cited Russian Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Kozak as saying on Friday.
snippet: Russia's Gazprom and Ukraine's Naftogaz will sign a new five-year agreement on transit of Russian gas to Europe via Ukraine, the RIA news agency cited Russian Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Kozak as saying on Friday.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Russia's Gazprom and Ukraine's Naftogaz will sign a new five-year agreement on transit of Russian gas to Europe via Ukraine, the RIA news agency cited Russian Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Kozak as saying on Friday.
headline_main: Russia Says to Sign Five-Year Gas Transit Deal With Ukraine-RIA
headline_print_headline: Russia Says to Sign Five-Year Gas Transit Deal With Ukraine-RIA

abstract: Euronext wheat was little changed on Friday in light trading ahead of the year-end holiday period while traders waited to see if strikes in France over pension reform would have a significant impact on exports.
snippet: Euronext wheat was little changed on Friday in light trading ahead of the year-end holiday period while traders waited to see if strikes in France over pension reform would have a significant impact on exports.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — Euronext wheat was little changed on Friday in light trading ahead of the year-end holiday period while traders waited to see if strikes in France over pension reform would have a significant impact on exports.
headline_main: EU Wheat in Quiet Pre-Holiday Trade as French Strikes Assessed
headline_print_headline: EU Wheat in Quiet Pre-Holiday Trade as French Strikes Assessed

abstract: Moscow and Kiev have signed agreements covering the supply of  Russian gas via Ukraine to Europe, a spokesman for Kremlin-controlled Gazprom said on Friday, marking a major step towards clinching a final deal.
snippet: Moscow and Kiev have signed agreements covering the supply of  Russian gas via Ukraine to Europe, a spokesman for Kremlin-controlled Gazprom said on Friday, marking a major step towards clinching a final deal.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW/KIEV — Moscow and Kiev have signed agreements covering the supply of Russian gas via Ukraine to Europe, a spokesman for Kremlin-controlled Gazprom said on Friday, marking a major step towards clinching a final deal.
headline_main: Russia, Ukraine Reach Deal Over Gas Transit to Europe
headline_print_headline: Russia, Ukraine Reach Deal Over Gas Transit to Europe

abstract: Alphabet Inc's newly instated Chief Executive Officer Sundar Pichai would receive a hefty $240 million in performance-based stock awards over the next three years, the highest ever promised to any executive of the search giant.
snippet: Alphabet Inc's newly instated Chief Executive Officer Sundar Pichai would receive a hefty $240 million in performance-based stock awards over the next three years, the highest ever promised to any executive of the search giant.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Alphabet Inc's newly instated Chief Executive Officer Sundar Pichai would receive a hefty $240 million in performance-based stock awards over the next three years, the highest ever promised to any executive of the search giant.
headline_main: Alphabet Grants Pichai Largest Ever Stock Award, Again
headline_print_headline: Alphabet Grants Pichai Largest Ever Stock Award, Again

abstract: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said his American counterpart Donald Trump assured him on Friday that he will not impose tariffs on the South American country's steel and aluminum.
snippet: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said his American counterpart Donald Trump assured him on Friday that he will not impose tariffs on the South American country's steel and aluminum.
lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO — Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro said his American counterpart Donald Trump assured him on Friday that he will not impose tariffs on the South American country's steel and aluminum.
headline_main: Bolsonaro Says U.S. Won't Impose Tariffs on Brazilian Steel
headline_print_headline: Bolsonaro Says U.S. Won't Impose Tariffs on Brazilian Steel

abstract: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — As Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar escalated their attacks on Pete Buttigieg in Thursday night’s Democratic debate, and Mr. Buttigieg forcefully pushed back, a crucial if unspoken fact was driving the political combat: All three candidates are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.

abstract: Chennedy Carter scored 21 points for her fourth straight 20-plus game and No. 11 Texas A&M beat Georgia Tech 60-48 on Friday in the Puerto Rico Coqui Classic.
